Treasury Secretary Tim Geithner and National Economic Council Director Larry Summers have convened official designees to the Presidential Task Force on the Auto Industry to discuss restructuring plans from Chrysler and General Motors. The Task Force, which includes various cabinet members and advisers, will focus on financial and operational restructuring, improving wage and benefit structures, and developing clean and competitive cars. Geithner and Summers emphasized the urgency of the situation and tasked the designees to conduct further analysis and provide recommendations for the next meeting. The designees include officials from various government departments, such as the Treasury Department, the Department of Labor, and the EPA.